{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846096125,"sessionID":"ses_2875631a0ffe1vwKTENdvGEajQ","part":{"id":"prt_d78a9ec79001aDeX3wI1KN1zmY","messageID":"msg_d78a9dd04001iLveM3y7uJvt0q","sessionID":"ses_2875631a0ffe1vwKTENdvGEajQ","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_1208f420f6e74a08a4bf4bd1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentd project structure","prompt":"Explore the project at /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z thoroughly to understand:\n\n1. The overall project structure - what directories exist, what is this project about\n2. Look for any existing specs, delta-spec.md files, or openspec files\n3. Search for anything related to \"agentd\", \"idle\", \"cleanup\", \"清理\", \"controller\" in the codebase\n4. Look at pkg/agentd directory if it exists\n5. Check for any existing controller implementations to understand patterns\n6. Look at the deployment specs mentioned in the prompt (deployment/client-go.md)\n7. Check for any AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter related code\n\nReturn a comprehensive summary of:\n- Project structure overview\n- What agentd is/does\n- Any existing idle cleanup related code or configuration\n- Controller patterns used in the project\n- Relevant types and interfaces from the codebase\n- Any existing spec files and their format","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_28755fa0cffeUKRCZunhwE476U (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nNow I have a thorough understanding of the project. Here is the comprehensive summary:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Project Summary\n\n### 1. Project Structure Overview\n\n**Project Name:** AgentCube (module: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`)\n\n**Purpose:** A Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents. It provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through session-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n\n**Top-Level Directory Structure:**\n```\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/\n├── cmd/                    # Binary entrypoints\n│   └── picod/              # PicoD in-sandbox daemon (cmd/agentd/ does NOT exist yet)\n├── pkg/                    # Go packages\n│   ├── apis/runtime/v1alpha1/   # CRD type definitions (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter)\n│   ├── common/             # Shared utilities\n│   ├── picod/              # In-sandbox daemon (HTTP server + file management + JWT auth)\n│   ├── router/             # Session-aware HTTP proxy/router\n│   ├── store/              # Redis/Valkey session storage layer\n│   └── workloadmanager/    # Workload manager (reconciler, handlers, lifecycle management)\n├── client-go/              # Generated Kubernetes client code (clientset, informers, listers)\n├── changes/                # Change requests AR-001 through AR-018\n├── deployment/             # Deployment specs (Helm, Docker, Makefile)\n├── idle-cleanup/           # Idle cleanup spec and design (for agentd)\n├── sandbox-orchestration/  # Sandbox orchestration specs\n├── session-routing/        # Session routing specs\n├── session-store/          # Session store specs\n├── cli-toolkit/            # CLI tool specs\n├── code-execution/         # Code execution specs\n├── python-sdk/             # Python SDK specs\n├── ci-cd/                  # CI/CD specs\n├── integrations/           # Integration specs\n├── testing/                # Testing specs\n├── delta-spec.md           # Root-level delta spec (AR-016: PicoD file management)\n├── design.md               # AR-016 design document\n├── project.md              # Project context document\n├── proposal.md             # Root proposal\n├── go.mod / go.sum         # Go module files\n└── .sdd_prompt.md          # SDD prompt for AR-018\n```\n\n**Tech Stack:**\n- Go 1.25, Gin HTTP framework\n- Kubernetes: CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime v0.22.2, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox`\n- Storage: Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go)\n- Auth: JWT RS256, K8s TokenReview\n- Packaging: Helm 3, multi-stage Docker, GitHub Actions CI/CD\n\n---\n\n### 2. What Agentd Is/Does\n\n**Agentd** (AR-018) is a **planned but not yet implemented** component -- an independent in-cluster Kubernetes controller for **idle sandbox cleanup**. Key facts:\n\n- **Module path:** `pkg/agentd` (directory does NOT exist yet)\n- **Binary path:** `cmd/agentd/main.go` (does NOT exist yet)\n- **Framework:** controller-runtime (Manager + Reconciler pattern)\n- **Watched resource:** `Sandbox` CR from `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/api/v1alpha1` (API group `agents.x-k8.io/v1alpha1`)\n- **Core logic:**\n  1. Watch Sandbox CR create/update events\n  2. Read `last-activity-time` annotation from Sandbox metadata\n  3. Parse as RFC3339, compute `expirationTime = lastActivity + 15 minutes`\n  4. If expired: delete the Sandbox\n  5. If not expired: `RequeueAfter: time.Until(expirationTime)`\n- **Constant:** `SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute`\n- **Design choice:** Uses controller-runtime watch (not polling), does NOT depend on Redis Store\n- **Relationship to existing code:** Complements `LifecycleManager` in workloadmanager (which does polling-based cleanup). Both can coexist as a two-layer cleanup guarantee.\n\n**Current AR-018 status:** Proposal is complete, design.md is a TODO stub, delta-spec.md is a TODO stub, tasks.md is a TODO stub. The `idle-cleanup/spec.md` and `idle-cleanup/design.md` files contain the actual detailed specification and design.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Existing Idle Cleanup Related Code and Configuration\n\n**Existing idle cleanup is in `pkg/workloadmanager/`:**\n\n- **`pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox_lifecycle.go`** -- `LifecycleManager` struct with polling-based cleanup\n  - `cleanupExpired()` -- TTL-based cleanup via `store.ListExpiredSandboxes()`\n  - `cleanupIdle()` -- Idle timeout cleanup via `store.ListInactiveSandboxes()`\n  - `cleanupOrphans()` -- Orphan CR cleanup\n  - `cleanupGhosts()` -- Ghost entry reconstruction\n  - Default check interval: 5 minutes\n  - Default idle timeout: 15 minutes (`DefaultIdleTimeout` in `constants.go`)\n\n- **`pkg/workloadmanager/handler/constants.go`** -- Key constants:\n  - `AnnotationIdleTimeout = \"runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout\"` -- duration string on Sandbox CR\n  - `DefaultIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute`\n  - `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15` (minutes, integer)\n  - GC cleanup reasons: `GRCleanupReasonTTLExpired`, `GRCleanupReasonIdle`, `GRCleanupReasonOrphanCR`, `GRCleanupReasonGhostEntry`\n\n- **Annotation key for agentd:** The idle-cleanup design doc references `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey` = `\"last-activity-time\"`, but this constant does NOT currently exist in the Go codebase. It is referenced in spec/design documents but needs to be defined. The annotation is written by the Router when proxying requests.\n\n- **`idle-cleanup/spec.md`** -- Complete idle cleanup spec with GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios\n- **`idle-cleanup/design.md`** -- Complete design with Reconciler struct, algorithm, SetupWithManager pattern, binary main.go structure\n\n---\n\n### 4. Controller Patterns Used in the Project\n\n**Pattern 1: WorkloadManager SandboxReconciler (informers + workqueue)**\n- Location: `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/reconciler.go`\n- Uses raw `k8s.io/client-go` informers (not controller-runtime)\n- Pattern: `SharedInformerFactory` -> `AddEventHandler` -> `workqueue.RateLimitingInterface` -> worker goroutines\n- Watches: AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, Pod\n- Event handlers: `onAgentRuntimeAdd/Update/Delete`, `onCodeInterpreterAdd/Update/Delete`, `onPodAdd/Update/Delete`\n- Lifecycle: `Run(stopCh)` starts informers, waits for cache sync, spawns workers, blocks on stopCh, drains workqueue\n\n**Pattern 2: controller-runtime Reconciler (planned for agentd)**\n- Location: `idle-cleanup/design.md` (design only, not implemented)\n- Pattern: `ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).For(&sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}).Complete(r)`\n- Reconciler struct embeds `client.Client` and holds `*runtime.Scheme`\n- Manager options: metrics disabled (`BindAddress: \"0\"`), health probe disabled\n- Signal-driven shutdown: `mgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler())`\n\n**Key difference:** The existing SandboxReconciler uses the lower-level client-go informer/workqueue pattern, while agentd will use the higher-level controller-runtime Reconciler pattern.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Relevant Types and Interfaces\n\n**CRD Types (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`):**\n- `AgentRuntime` -- Custom resource for agent runtimes\n- `CodeInterpreter` -- Custom resource for code interpreters (has `warmPoolSize`, `authMode`, `template`)\n- Both use API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n\n**Client-Go Generated (`client-go/`):**\n- `Clientset` with `RuntimeV1alpha1()` accessor\n- `AgentRuntimeInterface` / `CodeInterpreterInterface` -- typed REST clients with Create/Update/Delete/Get/List/Watch/Patch\n- `AgentRuntimeInformer` / `CodeInterpreterInformer` -- informer + lister\n- `AgentRuntimeLister` / `CodeInterpreterLister` -- read-only cache accessors\n- Fake clients for testing\n\n**Handler Types (`pkg/workloadmanager/handler/`):**\n- `SandboxInfo` -- session metadata (SessionID, SandboxName, Kind, PodIP, CreatedAt, ExpiresAt, Status, LastActivityAt)\n- `CreateSandboxRequest/Response` -- API request/response models\n- `MetricsRecorder` interface -- Prometheus metrics abstraction\n- GVR constants: `AgentRuntimeGVR`, `CodeInterpreterGVR`, `SandboxGVR`\n- Kind constants: `AgentRuntimeKind = \"AgentRuntime\"`, `CodeInterpreterKind = \"CodeInterpreter\"`\n- Label constants: `LabelSessionID = \"runtime.agentcube.io/session-id\"`, `LabelWorkloadName`, `LabelSandboxName`\n\n**Reconciler Types (`pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/`):**\n- `SandboxReconciler` -- main reconciler struct\n- `ReconcilerDeps` -- dependency injection struct (Clientset, InformerFactory, ARLister, CILister, PodInformer, Store, Workers, MetricsRecorder)\n- `Store` interface -- StoreSandbox, UpdateSandbox, DeleteSandboxBySessionID, GetSandbox, ListSandboxes\n- Status constants: `StatusPending`, `StatusRunning`, `StatusTerminated`\n\n**PicoD Types (`pkg/picod/`):**\n- `Config` -- Port, Workspace, FileConfig\n- `Server` -- Gin-based HTTP server\n- `AuthManager` -- JWT RS256 validation with RSA public key\n- `FileManager` interface -- file operations (ReadFile, WriteFile, StatFile, etc.)\n\n**Planned Agentd Types (from idle-cleanup/design.md):**\n```go\nvar SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n\ntype Reconciler struct {\n    client.Client\n    Scheme *runtime.Scheme\n}\n\nfunc (r *Reconciler) Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req ctrl.Request) (ctrl.Result, error)\nfunc (r *Reconciler) SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. Existing Spec Files and Their Format\n\n**Spec file locations:**\n- Root-level: `delta-spec.md` (AR-016: PicoD file management, 870 lines)\n- Per-component: `deployment/spec.md`, `idle-cleanup/spec.md`, `sandbox-orchestration/spec.md`, etc.\n- Per-change: `changes/AR-XXX/delta-spec.md` (AR-002 through AR-018)\n\n**OpenSpec delta-spec.md format:**\n```markdown\n# AR-XXX: Title — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n- **Module:** `pkg/xxx`\n- **Language:** Go\n- **Size:** S/M/L\n- **Base specs:** `path/to/base-spec.md`\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Descriptive name\n\nThe system SHALL ... (normative requirement with SHALL/SHOULD/MAY)\n\n#### Scenario: Descriptive scenario name\n\n- **GIVEN** <precondition>\n- **WHEN** <action>\n- **THEN** <expected outcome>\n```\n\n**Key conventions:**\n- Normative language: SHALL = mandatory, SHOULD = recommended, MAY = optional\n- Each requirement MUST have one or more GIVEN/WHEN/THEN acceptance scenarios\n- Go code snippets inline for type definitions\n- Tables for constants, HTTP status codes, config fields\n- AR-018's delta-spec.md is currently a TODO stub (only 20 lines with placeholder text)\n- The actual detailed spec for agentd is in `idle-cleanup/spec.md` (69 lines, complete)\n\n**Other change documents per AR:**\n- `proposal.md` -- Purpose, scope, architecture, impact analysis, alternatives, acceptance criteria\n- `design.md` -- Architecture, data structures, API contracts, implementation details, testing strategy\n- `tasks.md` -- Step-by-step implementation tasks with verification commands\n- `delta-spec.md` -- Formal requirements with GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_28755fa0cffeUKRCZunhwE476U","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentd project structure","time":{"start":1775845901807,"end":1775846096122}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775846096188,"sessionID":"ses_2875631a0ffe1vwKTENdvGEajQ","part":{"id":"prt_d78acfcfc001B1rYGo6XjmMsiN","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d78a9dd04001iLveM3y7uJvt0q","sessionID":"ses_2875631a0ffe1vwKTENdvGEajQ","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":19616,"input":19234,"output":284,"reasoning":98,"cache":{"write":0,"read":0}},"cost":0.005939266}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775846098332,"sessionID":"ses_2875631a0ffe1vwKTENdvGEajQ","part":{"id":"prt_d78ad0599001uy0dR67gvuL8pi","messageID":"msg_d78acfd54001X48v5RfYK9RseR","sessionID":"ses_2875631a0ffe1vwKTENdvGEajQ","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846100466,"sessionID":"ses_2875631a0ffe1vwKTENdvGEajQ","part":{"id":"prt_d78ad09f9001aJM8zQmy1FDapC","messageID":"msg_d78acfd54001X48v5RfYK9RseR","sessionID":"ses_2875631a0ffe1vwKTENdvGEajQ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_9bf98d92fbeb489299d4ff90","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/idle-cleanup/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/idle-cleanup/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Idle Cleanup Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Run a controller that deletes `Sandbox` custom resources when an idle-timeout annotation indicates the sandbox has been inactive beyond a fixed grace period.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Reconciliation trigger\n9: The system SHALL register a controller-runtime reconciler for resource kind `Sandbox` API version `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`, using the manager’s API reader/writer client for get/delete operations.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Sandbox watch drives reconcile\n12: - **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` object is created or updated in the cluster\n13: - **WHEN** the manager is running\n14: - **THEN** the reconciler `Reconcile` function is invoked with the object’s namespace and name\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Idle detection input\n17: The system SHALL read annotation key `last-activity-time` (constant `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey`) from the `Sandbox` metadata. When the annotation is missing or empty, the system SHALL take no delete action and SHALL return without requeue (unless other logic applies—none in this controller).\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: No annotation means no deletion\n20: - **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` without `last-activity-time`\n21: - **WHEN** reconciliation completes\n22: - **THEN** the sandbox is not deleted and result has zero `RequeueAfter`\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Idle detection parsing\n25: When the annotation is non-empty, the system SHALL parse it with `time.RFC3339`. On parse error, the system SHALL return `RequeueAfter: 30 seconds` and the parse error.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Invalid timestamp requeues\n28: - **GIVEN** annotation value is not RFC3339\n29: - **WHEN** `time.Parse` fails\n30: - **THEN** reconcile returns `(Result{RequeueAfter: 30s}, err)`\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Expiration threshold\n33: The system SHALL define `SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute`. The system SHALL compute `expirationTime = lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`. When `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`, the system SHALL delete the `Sandbox` resource.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Idle beyond 15 minutes triggers delete\n36: - **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` parses to a time more than 15 minutes in the past\n37: - **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n38: - **THEN** the controller calls delete on the `Sandbox` client object\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Not yet expired requeues until expiration\n41: - **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` is recent enough that expiration is in the future\n42: - **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n43: - **THEN** the result is `RequeueAfter: time.Until(expirationTime)` and no delete occurs\n44: \n45: ### Requirement: Delete idempotency\n46: When delete returns `NotFound`, the system SHALL treat it as success and SHALL return empty result with nil error. Other delete errors SHALL be returned to trigger retry.\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: Already deleted sandbox\n49: - **GIVEN** the API server returns not found on delete\n50: - **WHEN** the reconciler handles the error\n51: - **THEN** reconcile returns `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)`\n52: \n53: ### Requirement: Get not found\n54: When get returns `NotFound`, the system SHALL return empty result and nil error.\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: Sandbox removed before reconcile\n57: - **GIVEN** the sandbox no longer exists\n58: - **WHEN** `Get` fails with not found\n59: - **THEN** reconcile returns without error\n60: \n61: ## Requirements (binary / operator)\n62: \n63: ### Requirement: Manager options\n64: The `agentd` binary SHALL construct controller-runtime `Manager` with scheme containing core Kubernetes types and `sandboxv1alpha1` from `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/api/v1alpha1`, SHALL disable metrics server (`BindAddress: \"0\"`), and SHALL disable health probe server (`HealthProbeBindAddress: \"0\"`).\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: Signal-driven shutdown\n67: - **GIVEN** the process runs `mgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler())`\n68: - **WHEN** SIGTERM/SIGINT is received\n69: - **THEN** the manager stops gracefully per controller-runtime defaults\n\n(End of file - total 69 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Idle Cleanup Specification\n\n## Purpose\nRun a controller that deletes `Sandbox` custom resources when an idle-timeout annotation indicates the sandbox has been inactive beyond a fixed grace period.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Reconciliation trigger\nThe system SHALL register a controller-runtime reconciler for resource kind `Sandbox` API version `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`, using the manager’s API reader/writer client for get/delete operations.\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox watch drives reconcile\n- **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` object is created or updated in the cluster\n- **WHEN** the manager is running\n- **THEN** the reconciler `Reconcile` function is invoked with the object’s namespace and name\n\n### Requirement: Idle detection input\nThe system SHALL read annotation key `last-activity-time` (constant `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey`) from the `Sandbox` metadata. When the annotation is missing or empty, the system SHALL take no delete action and SHALL return without requeue (unless other logic applies—none in this controller).\n\n#### Scenario: No annotation means no deletion\n- **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` without `last-activity-time`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/idle-cleanup/spec.md","time":{"start":1775846100458,"end":1775846100464}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846101974,"sessionID":"ses_2875631a0ffe1vwKTENdvGEajQ","part":{"id":"prt_d78ad0e80001dwEqnRlVv2xnMS","messageID":"msg_d78acfd54001X48v5RfYK9RseR","sessionID":"ses_2875631a0ffe1vwKTENdvGEajQ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_f4bc53e937cc4e6bbacdfad5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/idle-cleanup/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/idle-cleanup/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Idle Cleanup — Design\n2: \n3: ## Module\n4: \n5: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` (see root `go.mod` in sandbox-orchestration design).\n6: \n7: ## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/agentd`\n8: \n9: ### Time threshold\n10: \n11: ```go\n12: var SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n13: ```\n14: \n15: Idle expiration: `expirationTime := lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`; delete when `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`.\n16: \n17: ### Annotation key\n18: \n19: The reconciler uses the same key as workload manager pod annotation for idle timeout tracking on the **Sandbox** object:\n20: \n21: - Import: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager`\n22: - Key: `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey` = **`\"last-activity-time\"`**\n23: \n24: (Workload manager also sets `runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout` on Sandbox metadata for template-driven idle configuration; **agentd** only reads `last-activity-time`.)\n25: \n26: ### Reconciler\n27: \n28: ```go\n29: package agentd\n30: \n31: type Reconciler struct {\n32:     client.Client\n33:     Scheme *runtime.Scheme\n34: }\n35: \n36: func (r *Reconciler) Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req ctrl.Request) (ctrl.Result, error)\n37: ```\n38: \n39: **Algorithm (exact behavior):**\n40: \n41: 1. `sandbox := &sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}`; `Get(ctx, req.NamespacedName, sandbox)`.\n42: 2. If `errors.IsNotFound(err)` → `return ctrl.Result{}, nil`.\n43: 3. If other get error → return `ctrl.Result{}, err`.\n44: 4. `lastActivityStr, exists := sandbox.Annotations[workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey]`.\n45: 5. If `exists && lastActivityStr != \"\"`:\n46:    - `lastActivity, err := time.Parse(time.RFC3339, lastActivityStr)`\n47:    - If parse err → `return ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: 30 * time.Second}, err`\n48:    - `expirationTime := lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`\n49:    - If `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`:\n50:      - `r.Delete(ctx, sandbox)`; if err and not `IsNotFound` → `return ctrl.Result{}, err`\n51:    - Else:\n52:      - `return ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: time.Until(expirationTime)}, nil`\n53: 6. `return ctrl.Result{}, nil`\n54: \n55: ### SetupWithManager\n56: \n57: ```go\n58: func (r *Reconciler) SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error {\n59:     return ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).\n60:         For(&sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}).\n61:         Complete(r)\n62: }\n63: ```\n64: \n65: ## Binary `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n66: \n67: ### Scheme registration\n68: \n69: ```go\n70: var schemeBuilder = runtime.NewScheme()\n71: \n72: func init() {\n73:     utilruntime.Must(scheme.AddToScheme(schemeBuilder))\n74:     utilruntime.Must(sandboxv1alpha1.AddToScheme(schemeBuilder))\n75: }\n76: ```\n77: \n78: ### Controller-runtime manager\n79: \n80: ```go\n81: mgr, err := ctrl.NewManager(ctrl.GetConfigOrDie(), ctrl.Options{\n82:     Scheme:                 schemeBuilder,\n83:     Metrics:                metricsserver.Options{BindAddress: \"0\"},\n84:     HealthProbeBindAddress:   \"0\",\n85: })\n86: ```\n87: \n88: ### Controller registration (duplicate of SetupWithManager pattern)\n89: \n90: ```go\n91: err = ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).\n92:     For(&sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}).\n93:     Complete(&agentd.Reconciler{\n94:         Client: mgr.GetClient(),\n95:         Scheme: mgr.GetScheme(),\n96:     })\n97: ```\n98: \n99: ### Run\n100: \n101: ```go\n102: mgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler())\n103: ```\n104: \n105: ## Watched resources\n106: \n107: | API group | Version | Kind | Trigger |\n108: |-----------|---------|------|---------|\n109: | `agents.x-k8s.io` | `v1alpha1` | `Sandbox` | Default `For()` watch — creates, updates, deletes (per controller-runtime) |\n110: \n111: No explicit `Owns` or `Watches` — single primary resource `Sandbox`.\n112: \n113: ## Related workload-manager constants (context)\n114: \n115: From `pkg/workloadmanager` (not used by agentd reconcile logic but set when sandboxes are created):\n116: \n117: - `IdleTimeoutAnnotationKey = \"runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout\"` — duration string on Sandbox CR.\n118: - `LastActivityAnnotationKey = \"last-activity-time\"` — **read by agentd** for idle cleanup.\n119: \n120: ## Dependencies\n121: \n122: - `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors`\n123: - `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime`\n124: - `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/api/v1alpha1`\n125: - `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime`\n126: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager` (annotation key only)\n\n(End of file - total 126 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Idle Cleanup — Design\n\n## Module\n\n- `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` (see root `go.mod` in sandbox-orchestration design).\n\n## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/agentd`\n\n### Time threshold\n\n```go\nvar SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n```\n\nIdle expiration: `expirationTime := lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`; delete when `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`.\n\n### Annotation key\n\nThe reconciler uses the same key as workload manager pod annotation for idle timeout tracking on the **Sandbox** object:\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/idle-cleanup/design.md","time":{"start":1775846101966,"end":1775846101972}}}}
