{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846126551,"sessionID":"ses_2875631a0ffe1vwKTENdvGEajQ","part":{"id":"prt_d78ad70270012fx2GdebvJbZUX","messageID":"msg_d78ad4919001NuOLkkOZukhfVw","sessionID":"ses_2875631a0ffe1vwKTENdvGEajQ","type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_522c2200ee714ffb85032c15","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"LastActivityAnnotationKey","path":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z"},"output":"Found 11 matches\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-018/proposal.md:\n  Line 25:    - 从 Sandbox 注解 `last-activity-time`（`workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey`）读取最后活动时间\n  Line 129: | `pkg/workloadmanager` | 仅引用 `LastActivityAnnotationKey` 常量 |\n  Line 210: 2. **注解引用**：使用 `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey`（值为 `\"last-activity-time\"`），避免魔法字符串\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/config.go:\n  Line 5: const LastActivityAnnotationKey = \"agentcube.volcano.sh/last-activity\"\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-009/tasks.md:\n  Line 14: - [ ] T-001.03 定义常量 `LastActivityAnnotationKey = \"agentcube.volcano.sh/last-activity\"`\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/sandbox-orchestration/design.md:\n  Line 328:     LastActivityAnnotationKey = \"last-activity-time\"\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/idle-cleanup/design.md:\n  Line 22: - Key: `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey` = **`\"last-activity-time\"`**\n  Line 44: 4. `lastActivityStr, exists := sandbox.Annotations[workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey]`.\n  Line 118: - `LastActivityAnnotationKey = \"last-activity-time\"` — **read by agentd** for idle cleanup.\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/idle-cleanup/spec.md:\n  Line 17: The system SHALL read annotation key `last-activity-time` (constant `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey`) from the `Sandbox` metadata. When the annotation is missing or empty, the system SHALL take no delete action and SHALL return without requeue (unless other logic applies—none in this controller).\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/session-routing/design.md:\n  Line 12: const LastActivityAnnotationKey = \"agentcube.volcano.sh/last-activity\"","metadata":{"matches":11,"truncated":false},"title":"LastActivityAnnotationKey","time":{"start":1775846126538,"end":1775846126547}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775846126576,"sessionID":"ses_2875631a0ffe1vwKTENdvGEajQ","part":{"id":"prt_d78ad73d6001FxTSvjp7JCB0k8","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d78ad4919001NuOLkkOZukhfVw","sessionID":"ses_2875631a0ffe1vwKTENdvGEajQ","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":45061,"input":44919,"output":83,"reasoning":59,"cache":{"write":0,"read":0}},"cost":0.012632086}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775846127926,"sessionID":"ses_2875631a0ffe1vwKTENdvGEajQ","part":{"id":"prt_d78ad7934001B7FdLaRw4U74pj","messageID":"msg_d78ad740b001MR3XsyMmlVwmVf","sessionID":"ses_2875631a0ffe1vwKTENdvGEajQ","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846212344,"sessionID":"ses_2875631a0ffe1vwKTENdvGEajQ","part":{"id":"prt_d78ada60a001ISWdAiAK4JQWYu","messageID":"msg_d78ad740b001MR3XsyMmlVwmVf","sessionID":"ses_2875631a0ffe1vwKTENdvGEajQ","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_a95c3e2a1fca40a1b1efed51","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-018: Agentd 空闲清理控制器 — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `pkg/agentd`, `cmd/agentd`\n- **Language:** Go\n- **Size:** S\n- **Base specs:** `idle-cleanup/spec.md`, `deployment/client-go.md`\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Reconciler watches Sandbox CR\n\nThe system SHALL register a controller-runtime reconciler for resource kind `Sandbox` API group `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`. The reconciler SHALL be triggered on Sandbox create and update events via `ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).For(&sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}).Complete(r)`.\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox creation triggers reconcile\n\n- **GIVEN** the agentd manager is running\n- **WHEN** a new `Sandbox` object is created in the cluster\n- **THEN** the reconciler `Reconcile` function is invoked with the object's namespace and name\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox update triggers reconcile\n\n- **GIVEN** the agentd manager is running\n- **WHEN** an existing `Sandbox` object is updated (including annotation changes)\n- **THEN** the reconciler `Reconcile` function is invoked with the object's namespace and name\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox deletion triggers reconcile\n\n- **GIVEN** the agentd manager is running\n- **WHEN** a `Sandbox` object is deleted from the cluster\n- **THEN** the reconciler `Reconcile` function is invoked and returns `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)` without error\n\n### Requirement: Reconciler data structures\n\nThe system SHALL define the following types in `pkg/agentd`:\n\n```go\nvar SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n\ntype Reconciler struct {\n    client.Client\n    Scheme *runtime.Scheme\n}\n```\n\n`SessionExpirationTimeout` SHALL be the fixed idle expiration threshold. The `Reconciler` struct SHALL embed `client.Client` for API server operations and hold a `*runtime.Scheme` for type registration.\n\n#### Scenario: SessionExpirationTimeout is 15 minutes\n\n- **GIVEN** the `pkg/agentd` package is imported\n- **WHEN** `SessionExpirationTimeout` is read\n- **THEN** its value equals `15 * time.Minute`\n\n#### Scenario: Reconciler embeds client.Client\n\n- **GIVEN** a `Reconciler` instance is constructed\n- **WHEN** the instance is used\n- **THEN** it can call `Get`, `Delete`, and other `client.Client` methods directly\n\n### Requirement: Get Sandbox and handle not found\n\nThe `Reconcile` method SHALL retrieve the `Sandbox` object using `r.Get(ctx, req.NamespacedName, sandbox)`. When the API server returns `NotFound`, the reconciler SHALL return `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)` without error.\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox no longer exists\n\n- **GIVEN** a reconcile request for namespace `\"default\"`, name `\"sandbox-abc\"`\n- **WHEN** `r.Get` returns `errors.IsNotFound(err)`\n- **THEN** reconcile returns `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)`\n\n#### Scenario: API server error on Get\n\n- **GIVEN** a reconcile request for a valid Sandbox\n- **WHEN** `r.Get` returns a non-NotFound error (e.g., connection refused)\n- **THEN** reconcile returns `(ctrl.Result{}, err)` to trigger retry\n\n### Requirement: Idle detection via annotation\n\nThe system SHALL read annotation key `last-activity-time` (constant `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey`) from the Sandbox metadata. When the annotation is missing or empty, the system SHALL return `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)` without delete action or requeue.\n\nThe constant `LastActivityAnnotationKey` SHALL be defined in `pkg/workloadmanager` with value `\"last-activity-time\"`.\n\n#### Scenario: Annotation is missing\n\n- **GIVEN** a Sandbox with no `last-activity-time` annotation\n- **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n- **THEN** the reconciler returns `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)` and the Sandbox is not deleted\n\n#### Scenario: Annotation is empty string\n\n- **GIVEN** a Sandbox with `last-activity-time: \"\"`\n- **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n- **THEN** the reconciler returns `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)` and the Sandbox is not deleted\n\n### Requirement: Timestamp parsing\n\nWhen the `last-activity-time` annotation is non-empty, the system SHALL parse it with `time.RFC3339`. On parse error, the system SHALL return `(ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: 30 * time.Second}, err)`.\n\n#### Scenario: Valid RFC3339 timestamp\n\n- **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` is `\"2026-04-10T10:00:00Z\"`\n- **WHEN** `time.Parse(time.RFC3339, ...)` is called\n- **THEN** parsing succeeds and returns the corresponding `time.Time` value\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid timestamp format\n\n- **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` is `\"not-a-timestamp\"`\n- **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n- **THEN** the reconciler returns `(ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: 30s}, err)` where `err` is the parse error\n\n#### Scenario: Partial RFC3339 timestamp\n\n- **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` is `\"2026-04-10\"`\n- **WHEN** `time.Parse(time.RFC3339, ...)` is called\n- **THEN** parsing fails and reconcile returns `(ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: 30s}, err)`\n\n### Requirement: Expiration threshold and delete\n\nThe system SHALL compute `expirationTime = lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`. When `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`, the system SHALL call `r.Delete(ctx, sandbox)` to remove the Sandbox resource.\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox idle beyond 15 minutes\n\n- **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` parses to `2026-04-10T10:00:00Z` and current time is `2026-04-10T10:16:00Z`\n- **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n- **THEN** `expirationTime` is `2026-04-10T10:15:00Z`, `time.Now().After(expirationTime)` is true, and `r.Delete` is called\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox not yet expired\n\n- **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` parses to `2026-04-10T10:00:00Z` and current time is `2026-04-10T10:05:00Z`\n- **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n- **THEN** `expirationTime` is `2026-04-10T10:15:00Z`, `time.Now().After(expirationTime)` is false, and no delete occurs\n\n#### Scenario: Exactly at expiration boundary\n\n- **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` parses to `2026-04-10T10:00:00Z` and current time is `2026-04-10T10:15:00Z`\n- **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n- **THEN** `time.Now().After(expirationTime)` is false (equal, not after), and result is `RequeueAfter` with a small positive duration or zero\n\n### Requirement: Requeue until expiration\n\nWhen the Sandbox is not yet expired, the system SHALL return `(ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: time.Until(expirationTime)}, nil)` to schedule the next reconciliation at the exact expiration time.\n\n#### Scenario: RequeueAfter is positive duration\n\n- **GIVEN** `expirationTime` is 10 minutes in the future\n- **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n- **THEN** the result is `ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: ~10m}` and `Requeue` is false\n\n#### Scenario: RequeueAfter approaches zero near expiration\n\n- **GIVEN** `expirationTime` is 1 second in the future\n- **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n- **THEN** the result is `ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: ~1s}`\n\n### Requirement: Delete idempotency\n\nWhen `r.Delete` returns `NotFound`, the system SHALL treat it as success and return `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)`. Other delete errors SHALL be returned as `(ctrl.Result{}, err)` to trigger retry.\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox already deleted by another controller\n\n- **GIVEN** the LifecycleManager deleted the Sandbox between reconcile Get and Delete\n- **WHEN** `r.Delete` returns `errors.IsNotFound(err)`\n- **THEN** reconcile returns `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)`\n\n#### Scenario: Delete fails with transient error\n\n- **GIVEN** the API server returns a connection error on Delete\n- **WHEN** `r.Delete` is called\n- **THEN** reconcile returns `(ctrl.Result{}, err)` to trigger retry\n\n### Requirement: Successful delete result\n\nWhen `r.Delete` succeeds (returns nil error), the system SHALL return `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)`.\n\n#### Scenario: Delete succeeds\n\n- **GIVEN** the Sandbox exists and is expired\n- **WHEN** `r.Delete` returns nil\n- **THEN** reconcile returns `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)`\n\n### Requirement: SetupWithManager\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `SetupWithManager` method on `Reconciler` that registers the controller with the manager:\n\n```go\nfunc (r *Reconciler) SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error {\n    return ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).\n        For(&sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}).\n        Complete(r)\n}\n```\n\n#### Scenario: Controller is registered\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid `ctrl.Manager`\n- **WHEN** `r.SetupWithManager(mgr)` is called\n- **THEN** the function returns `nil` and the controller is registered to watch Sandbox resources\n\n### Requirement: Binary entry point — Scheme registration\n\nThe `cmd/agentd/main.go` SHALL construct a scheme containing core Kubernetes types and `sandboxv1alpha1` from `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/api/v1alpha1`:\n\n```go\nvar schemeBuilder = runtime.NewScheme()\n\nfunc init() {\n    utilruntime.Must(scheme.AddToScheme(schemeBuilder))\n    utilruntime.Must(sandboxv1alpha1.AddToScheme(schemeBuilder))\n}\n```\n\n#### Scenario: Scheme contains core and Sandbox types\n\n- **GIVEN** the `init` function has run\n- **WHEN** `schemeBuilder` is inspected\n- **THEN** it recognizes both core `v1.Pod` and `sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox` types\n\n### Requirement: Binary entry point — Manager configuration\n\nThe binary SHALL construct a controller-runtime Manager with the following options:\n\n```go\nmgr, err := ctrl.NewManager(ctrl.GetConfigOrDie(), ctrl.Options{\n    Scheme:                 schemeBuilder,\n    Metrics:                metricsserver.Options{BindAddress: \"0\"},\n    HealthProbeBindAddress: \"0\",\n})\n```\n\nMetrics server SHALL be disabled (`BindAddress: \"0\"`). Health probe server SHALL be disabled (`HealthProbeBindAddress: \"0\"`).\n\n#### Scenario: Manager starts without metrics or health endpoints\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid kubeconfig is available\n- **WHEN** `ctrl.NewManager` is called with the specified options\n- **THEN** no metrics or health probe HTTP servers are started\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid kubeconfig fails fast\n\n- **GIVEN** no valid kubeconfig is available\n- **WHEN** `ctrl.GetConfigOrDie()` is called\n- **THEN** the process exits with a non-zero status\n\n### Requirement: Binary entry point — Controller registration and startup\n\nThe binary SHALL register the reconciler and start the manager:\n\n```go\nif err := (&agentd.Reconciler{\n    Client: mgr.GetClient(),\n    Scheme: mgr.GetScheme(),\n}).SetupWithManager(mgr); err != nil {\n    // exit with error\n}\n\nif err := mgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler()); err != nil {\n    // exit with error\n}\n```\n\n#### Scenario: Signal-driven graceful shutdown\n\n- **GIVEN** the manager is running\n- **WHEN** SIGTERM or SIGINT is received\n- **THEN** `ctrl.SetupSignalHandler()` triggers graceful shutdown and `mgr.Start` returns\n\n### Requirement: Package layout\n\nThe system SHALL organize code as follows:\n\n```\ncmd/agentd/\n└── main.go              — Binary entry point\npkg/agentd/\n├── reconciler.go        — Reconciler struct, Reconcile, SetupWithManager\n├── reconciler_test.go   — Unit tests\n└── const.go             — SessionExpirationTimeout constant\n```\n\n#### Scenario: Package compiles\n\n- **GIVEN** all files are in place\n- **WHEN** `go build ./cmd/agentd/` is run\n- **THEN** the build succeeds and produces an `agentd` binary\n\n#### Scenario: Package tests pass\n\n- **GIVEN** all test cases are implemented\n- **WHEN** `go test ./pkg/agentd/...` is run\n- **THEN** all tests pass with exit code 0\n\n### Requirement: Reconcile algorithm completeness\n\nThe `Reconcile` method SHALL implement the following algorithm exactly:\n\n1. `sandbox := &sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}`; `r.Get(ctx, req.NamespacedName, sandbox)`\n2. If `errors.IsNotFound(err)` → `return ctrl.Result{}, nil`\n3. If other get error → `return ctrl.Result{}, err`\n4. `lastActivityStr, exists := sandbox.Annotations[workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey]`\n5. If `!exists || lastActivityStr == \"\"` → `return ctrl.Result{}, nil`\n6. `lastActivity, err := time.Parse(time.RFC3339, lastActivityStr)`\n7. If parse error → `return ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: 30 * time.Second}, err`\n8. `expirationTime := lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`\n9. If `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`:\n   - `err := r.Delete(ctx, sandbox)`\n   - If err and not `errors.IsNotFound(err)` → `return ctrl.Result{}, err`\n   - `return ctrl.Result{}, nil`\n10. Else → `return ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: time.Until(expirationTime)}, nil`\n\n#### Scenario: Full happy path — expired sandbox deleted\n\n- **GIVEN** a Sandbox with `last-activity-time` set to 20 minutes ago\n- **WHEN** `Reconcile` is called\n- **THEN** steps 1-9 execute, `Delete` is called, and `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)` is returned\n\n#### Scenario: Full happy path — not yet expired requeues\n\n- **GIVEN** a Sandbox with `last-activity-time` set to 5 minutes ago\n- **WHEN** `Reconcile` is called\n- **THEN** steps 1-8 and 10 execute, returning `RequeueAfter: ~10m`\n\n#### Scenario: Missing annotation short-circuits\n\n- **GIVEN** a Sandbox without `last-activity-time`\n- **WHEN** `Reconcile` is called\n- **THEN** steps 1-5 execute, returning `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)` at step 5\n\n### Requirement: Code quality gates\n\nThe codebase SHALL pass the following checks after implementation:\n\n- `go vet ./pkg/agentd/... ./cmd/agentd/...` produces no warnings\n- `go test ./pkg/agentd/...` passes all tests\n- `go mod tidy` results in no changes\n\n#### Scenario: go vet clean\n\n- **GIVEN** AR-018 is implemented\n- **WHEN** `go vet ./pkg/agentd/... ./cmd/agentd/...` is run\n- **THEN** no warnings or errors are reported\n\n#### Scenario: All tests pass\n\n- **GIVEN** AR-018 is implemented\n- **WHEN** `go test ./pkg/agentd/...` is run\n- **THEN** all tests pass with exit code 0\n\n#### Scenario: No unused dependencies\n\n- **GIVEN** AR-018 is implemented\n- **WHEN** `go mod tidy` is run\n- **THEN** `go.mod` and `go.sum` are unchanged\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-018/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/reconciler.go\">\nERROR [78:24] cannot use (func() literal) (value of type func()) as func(interface{}) value in argument to runtime.HandleCrash\nERROR [83:24] cannot use (func() literal) (value of type func()) as func(interface{}) value in argument to runtime.HandleCrash\nERROR [88:24] cannot use (func() literal) (value of type func()) as func(interface{}) value in argument to runtime.HandleCrash\nERROR [97:24] cannot use (func() literal) (value of type func()) as func(interface{}) value in argument to runtime.HandleCrash\nERROR [102:24] cannot use (func() literal) (value of type func()) as func(interface{}) value in argument to runtime.HandleCrash\nERROR [107:24] cannot use (func() literal) (value of type func()) as func(interface{}) value in argument to runtime.HandleCrash\nERROR [116:25] cannot use (func() literal) (value of type func()) as func(interface{}) value in argument to runtime.HandleCrash\nERROR [121:25] cannot use (func() literal) (value of type func()) as func(interface{}) value in argument to runtime.HandleCrash\nERROR [126:25] cannot use (func() literal) (value of type func()) as func(interface{}) value in argument to runtime.HandleCrash\nERROR [153:13] cannot use stopCh (variable of type <-chan struct{}) as chan struct{} value in assignment\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/agentruntime.go\">\nERROR [51:25] undefined: LabelSessionID\nERROR [77:29] undefined: LabelSandboxName\nERRO